The paper focuses on enhancing the performance of Convolutional Neural Networks for text recognition, which is a task related to computer vision and natural language processing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Additionally, the paper proposes a new CNN framework and discusses the technical details of its construction, which suggests that it could also be relevant to categories such as cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also mentions the use of residual learning and dense feature fusion, which are techniques commonly used in deep learning and could make the paper relevant to categories such as cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
